title: Multiple missed blocks, erigon return null result
body:
#### System information

Erigon version: 
```
$ erigon --version
erigon version 2022.99.99-dev-eb07ad89
```

OS & Version: 
```
$ cat /etc/lsb-release
DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu
DISTRIB_RELEASE=20.04
DISTRIB_CODENAME=focal
DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Ubuntu 20.04.3 LTS"
```

Commit hash : -

#### Expected behavior and Steps to reproduce the behaviour 
All blocks should be chain 

#### Actual behaviour
We are seeing some missed blocks.
So, just `'{"method":"eth_getBlockByNumber","params":["0xecd52f",false],"id":1,"jsonrpc":"2.0"}'` return `null`
```
for ip in ${erigon[@]} ; 
do 
    printf "$ip\t" 
    curl --header 'Content-Type: application/json' --data-raw '{"method":"eth_blockNumber","params":[],"id":1,"jsonrpc":"2.0"}'  http://$ip:8545 -s --max-time 2 | jq -r .result | python3 -c "print(int(input(), base=16), end='')"
    printf "\t"
    curl --header 'Content-Type: application/json' --data-raw '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"web3_clientVersion","params":[],"id":1}' http://$ip:8545 -s --max-time 2 | jq .result | tr '\n' ' ' 
    printf "\t"
    curl --data '{"method":"eth_getBlockByNumber","params":["0xecd52f",false],"id":1,"jsonrpc":"2.0"}' -H "Content-Type: application/json" http://$ip:8545 -s --max-time 2  | jq .result  | tr '\n' ' ' | cut -c 1-50

 done
```
that returns something like
```
IP1    16506334    "erigon/2022.99.99/linux-amd64/go1.17.8"     null
IP2   16506334    "erigon/2022.99.99/linux-amd64/go1.17.8"     null
IP3    16506334    "erigon/2022.99.99/linux-amd64/go1.17.8"     null
IP4    16506334    "erigon/2022.99.99/linux-amd64/go1.17.8"     null
```

And there are a lot of such blocks.
I started to scan the network block by block from Genesys block.
I will share the blocks list I found.

#### Backtrace

There are no backtraces.

Ok, the range `1-14981500` is consistent.
In the range `14981500-15000000` I found 2 missed blocks.
In the range `15000000-latest` I found like ~1000 missed random blocks.
Which chain ?
Do you get the same result if you remove the `-s` and `--max-time` from the curl commands?

Ahh, sorry, I forgot to mention this.
